Peru 1999

Primera División

Note: an Apertura and a Clausura championship is played; the winners
are qualified for the Copa Libertadores 2000 and play off (3 matches)
for the 1999 title.  The third Copa Libertadores place goes to the team 
with the best aggregate record (bar Apertura and Clausura champions).

If the same team wins both tournaments, it wins the championship.  In
that case, the second and third place for the Copa Libertadores go to
the teams with the best aggregate records (bar the champions).

The team with the worst record in Apertura and Clausura together is 
relegated and replaced by the Copa Perú winners.

The team with the one but worst record will play off against the Segunda
Division champions.

